name: Valley View

reviews.review_text:
Food was really good, we had ordered kingfish thali, chonak thali, butter chicken, Paratha and lemon drinks.. the fish size was really big and tasty and worth the try.. i would give it 5/5 on food.. they also serve alcohol.

The only pain was their service, we had ordered 6 chonak and one kingfish thali and they prepared it vice versa.. the waiter came to ask of we were fine to have 5 kingfish thalis but when we denied he readily and politely agreed to rectify their mistake.. but very soon another waiter arrived with kingfish thalis and he had no clue.. so their internal communication was little off...we had ordered one lemon drink without sugar but even that was missed..

Overall food is awesome.. just waiters need to communicate internally better..

This place is close to the highway with lot of parking area. There are many steps to climb to the restaurant so it is little difficult for aged members. We visited this place on 1 June 2024 for lunch. We tried the Goan chonak and modso thali with vellyo rawa fry. The thali consisted of rice, prawn curry, bhindi bhaji, one piece of fish, kismoor, shevyo, sol kadi, salad, pickle and papad. I was disappointed with the salad served in the thali as it was all cut cabbage and one piece of carrot. However, the fried fish in the thali was fresh. The sweet in the thali was tasteless. The vellyo fry  was not that fresh but had a little better salad with some tomato and onion pieces. I found the thali a little expensive for the quality and quantity. The service was so slow that we had to wait for an hour till the food arrived. The staff is not welcoming at all.

Valley View Restaurant and Bar It is conveniently located across from the highway, where you will find the best seafood here.
People do come over to this place to have their various dishes,and it never disappoints them.
It is one of the best restaurants to visit in Goa and enjoy your various cuisines.
Goa is famous for its natural beauty, where people enjoy the weather anytime they come over to chill.
The restaurant has an amazing atmosphere with natural views just like the forest around it and cool vibes to enjoy together with friends and family. It tends to make you feel like having your meal with greenery all around you and also enjoy it while sharing your thoughts and love.
It has ample parking space as well for all vehicles.
The place is big enough to enjoy the natural view as they have an amazing ground beside the restaurant that makes it a little eye-catching to watch.
The restaurant has an outdoor seating area that is quiet and warm as well.
We tried out king fish (king mackerel). In spite of the fish being masala fried, you could specifically taste the fish.
Now you would be surprised to know why I said so. I have tried out many fish dishes where they just have a taste of masala, but this fish had a perfect blend of Indian spices on the fish and tasted yummy. The squid was delicious.
Another surprise was that we got 4 slices of beautiful fish and it just cost us Rs.400, whereas it would cost you around Rs.1000+ in Mumbai.
The taste of the food is really awesome, and you should definitely try out their seafood menu.
The service staff were really nice and interactive. I enjoyed spending time at this restaurant.

description:
### Valley View Restaurant Review

Nestled in Cuncolim, Goa, Valley View Restaurant boasts a commendable rating of 3.9, with a notable 768 reviews echoing a lively mix of opinions. This establishment is often celebrated for its **seafood** offerings, with a particular nod to their **kingfish** and **chonak thalis**, alongside its **highway** proximity and ample **parking** facilities, making it a favorite pit stop for locals and travelers alike.

#### Ambiance & Design

As you approach Valley View, you are greeted by a charming exterior and lush greenery, emanating a rustic yet inviting vibe. The restaurant features a two-tier structure with multiple steps leading up, providing a stunning **natural view** filled with forest-like surroundings that create a serene dining atmosphere. Customers frequently mention that the **outdoor seating area** is a highlightâ€”quiet and breezy, it allows diners to enjoy their meals while soaking in the beauty of the Goan landscape. Reviewers have conveyed an appreciation for the spacious layout, indicating that it suits both family gatherings and leisurely lunches with friends.

#### Menu & Culinary Experience

The menu at Valley View is notable for its seafood specialties. Diners rave about dishes such as the **kingfish thali** and the **Goan chonak**, with their rich flavors and generous portions often making them a worthy indulgence. 

One reviewer particularly praised the **kingfish**, mentioning that even though it was masala fried, the fresh fishâ€™s flavor shone through, reminiscent of authentic Goan cuisine. Other dishes like the **prawn curry**, **bhindi bhaji**, and **sol kadi** in the thalis have also received positive remarks for their bold and robust flavors. However, not all feedback has been glowing; some customers noted that the salad served in the thali could use more variety and freshness. 

Visually, the food presentation is engaging, often showcasing vibrant colors that capture the essence of Goan culinary traditions. The outdoor dining setups further enhance the experience, allowing diners to enjoy their meals while appreciating their picturesque surroundings.

#### Customer Experience & Service

Customer service at Valley View appears to be a mixed bag. While many guests appreciated the friendliness of the staff, others experienced inconsistencies in service efficiency. Some reviews highlighted a few hiccups, including mistakes with orders and slow delivery timesâ€”one patron reported waiting an hour for their meal. Despite these service delays, staff members have shown a willingness to rectify issues when raised, showcasing an intent to maintain customer satisfaction. A notable aspect is the restaurant's ability to accommodate reservations and walk-ins, although the steps leading to the dining area may pose a challenge for elderly guests.

#### Popularity & Reviews

The restaurant has cultivated a reputation that resonates with a broad audience. Guests frequently comment on the ample **parking area**, which is a practical boon for those visiting from the highway. On social media, the buzz around Valley View often emphasizes its seafood dishes, with photos of vibrant thalis and the serene ambience drawing attention.

The overall sentiment in customer feedback suggests that while the culinary experience is often delightful, improvements in service and consistency would elevate the dining experience significantly. 

#### Utilizing Visual Content

Many reviews share stunning visuals that highlight the restaurant's ambiance and dishes. From mouth-watering images of the **kingfish thali** to the inviting outdoor seating arrangements, these photos underline the charming experience Valley View has to offer. The greenery juxtaposed against delicious plates of seafood makes for an appealing sight, reflecting the melding of great food and beautiful natural surroundings.

In conclusion, Valley View Restaurant stands as a worthwhile destination in Cuncolim for its flavorful seafood offerings and potential for a relaxing dining experience amidst Goa's natural beauty. With ongoing attention to service quality, it could easily transition from being a valued pit-stop to a must-visit culinary gem.
